</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>ACR156:v97#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="ACR156"/><meta name="dc:title" content="ACR &#xA;              156-&#xA;                CHAPTERED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div width="100%" style="text-align:center;"><div id="bill_num_title_chap"><span style="text-align:center;font-weight:bold;font-size:1.1em;font-family:'Times New Roman'; "><b>
                Assembly Concurrent Resolution
              
                        No. 156</b></span></div><div style="text-align:center;padding-top: 1.0em;padding-bottom: 1.2em;" id="chap_num_title_chap"><span style="font-size:1.4em;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;">
                      CHAPTER 48</span></div></div><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to National Day of Play. </span></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center">
                  
                  [<span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Filed with
              </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Secretary of State
              </span> <span style="font-size: 13pt">April 21, 2026.
                      </span>]
                </div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">ACR 156, Hoover.
                          National Day of Play. </span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would recognize National Day of Play on March 21, 2026. </div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_601CA2CC-F75B-4603-AB11-97AD937ED9F2"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The Surgeon General of the United States has formally declared an epidemic of loneliness and social isolation, highlighting its health impacts, such as higher risk for anxiety, depression, heart disease, and dementia, and a shorter life span; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_8E0A382F-8AAD-4E0B-8DD4-0269511EA5B4"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, People are spending less time with family and friends and are less involved in their communities; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_908BB644-74DB-49AE-8884-BCF79928F540"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, A 2022 study found that families spend a significant portion of shared physical spaces in alone-together time, meaning individuals are present, but engaged in their own activities, such as using electronic devices; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_6CDB76B4-C0C2-4538-B128-D003D55E94B3"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Studies suggest that 21 percent of adults in the United States feel lonely; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_0AE53CAF-9FA1-4077-9BF6-8212EAF3E74D"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Only about one in three adults receives the recommended amount of physical activity each week, with less than 5 percent participating in 30 minutes of activity each day; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_1179D428-4F4F-4365-88F7-E6296BA3BF92"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Community-focused events, shared activities that require collaboration, and acts of service for the common good can bring a community together and promote social connection; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_3E6B5068-F0D8-4030-B588-4CE577E6B8DA"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Social connectedness reflects the continuum of meeting social connection needs; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_507C02A8-4A34-481C-93A3-C2F1C142DA45"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Social connection can help reduce the risk of chronic disease and serious illness; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_70917A7A-94E8-4D05-AAD2-F56BC8301850"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Social connection can improve our ability to manage stress, anxiety, and depression; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_52D59B22-4DE4-4929-AA49-B375EDC2B2E9"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Social connection encourages healthy eating habits and physical activity; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_13D93D44-DE38-4FC3-9EAB-DAC45DE3B5FC"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Important communities, such as neighborhoods, schools, places of worship, workplaces, and parks and recreation centers, offer social connections; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_B8709221-6E83-44C4-9279-2C0563938AA3"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, “Play” can be defined as an activity that is self-chosen, intrinsically motivated, and conducted in an active, but relatively stress-free, frame of mind; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_A63074B5-896F-4998-B95F-077130FD940B"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Play is fundamentally connected to social connection, as it provides space to develop and practice essential social skills, such as communication, cooperation, empathy, and negotiation; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_307B1F2A-0711-44D8-9290-EFB32B571E15"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Play promotes brain development, executive function skills, stress reduction, creativity, and problem-solving skills, while also strengthening relationships and fostering healthy social-emotional growth; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_646C277E-D426-4DC3-B744-5420471CCE58"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Play is a proven stress reliever for both children and adults, promoting overall well-being; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_70E5E68A-210E-4D10-BE8B-5966B73DDBEC"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Play reduces obesity and associated diseases; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_51E8319A-013E-4910-859D-0565D21D6E72"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Children today spend up to 35 percent less time playing freely outdoors due to a combination of factors, including increased screen time; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_BFEDB118-EB9A-483B-9FC2-6B269AABEDB9"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Excessive device use has detrimental physical and mental health impacts; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_8BFA7760-E2CA-45F8-BF5A-BEBB2DF79A5C"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Long-term consequences of excessive device use include impaired social development and cognitive function, particularly in children; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_9184BE53-172A-4818-984E-0694F7AE5D26"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Excessive device use can foster an absent presence, in which individuals are physically together, but mentally disengaged, leading to reduced quality in face-to-face interactions and increased feelings of social isolation; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_90E979DF-B1F6-40AD-A143-A56D501C025A"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Taking a break from electronics and screen time can provide significant physical, mental, and social benefits; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_6D04B7F0-71B5-43BD-83CB-6B30B7D29044"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, A National Day of Play advocates for and celebrates the essential role of play and social connections; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_F3D39F26-434C-4CCA-AB82-0635A7697AD0"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, A National Day of Play encourages individuals to put down their devices and participate in community-organized events; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_721D5A20-FB89-468B-8D3E-5289441ABD94"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, A National Day of Play strengthens community bonds and encourages a focus on creating safe and healthy environments for all; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_FAB50CBB-C724-44C0-A71B-8C2CE402C321"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The spring equinox represents the official start of spring in the Northern Hemisphere, signifying rebirth, renewal, and balance; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_C03E4ACC-4CF6-4082-BFC7-84D964C4A56F"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The spring equinox marks when days begin to get longer; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_57AF8038-B3D7-45B7-9EB4-349722F5157D"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, March 21, 2026, is the first Saturday after the spring equinox; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_D93EB754-ACFB-44AE-A7F8-02C8AAB521C4"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Assembly of the State of California, the Senate thereof concurring, That the Legislature recognizes National Day of Play on March 21st, 2026; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_E7BFE742-D446-484C-86B3-2AE246E4987C"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Legislature expresses support for Congress’s annual designation of the first Saturday after the spring equinox as National Day of Play; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_A10A4B7E-5B56-4F05-A14B-408E412DCB28"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Legislature recognizes the importance of social connection for mental, physical, and social development, and encourages people to put their electronics down and play; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_74EA55EF-0D53-414A-B3AA-05BA0A371792"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly transmit copies of this resolution to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
